SIMPLE: flaky
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flaky
<hw>Flak"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting
of flakes or of small, loose masses; lying, or cleaving off, in flakes
or layers; flakelike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What showers of mortal hail, what <qex>flaky</qex> fires!</q>
<rj><qau>Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>flaky</qex> weight of winter's purest snows.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>prone to strange or erratic behavior; -- of
persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>odd, unpredictable or unconventional; offbeat;
whacky; -- of behavior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>unpredictable, erratic, or unreliable; -- of
machinery, especially electronic devices.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧a
<xex>flaky</xex> computer board.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flam</ent>⟦br⟧
